results.name: Potential_Control_Line
results.title: Potential Control Line
results.snippet: A Potential Control Location (PCL) analysis was performed for a landscape encompassing both the Pike and San Isabel and Arapaho and Roosevelt National Forests by the Colorado Forest Restoration Institute closely following the methods of O’Connor et al. (2017). A PCL analysis maps the average probability of fire control for each pixel based on the association between historical fire interior and edge locations relative to landscape factors that influence containment such as presence of barriers to fire spread, resistance to control, potential fire behavior, topography, and accessibility. High PCL indicates good probability of success whereas low PCL indicates poor probability of success. The PCL map was referenced during the POD delineation process.The fourmost important variables in the model were distance to roads, distance to barriers (streams and large non-burnable patches), cost distance from major roads (firefighter accessibility), and resistance to control (inverse of fireline production rate).
